! conclusion: Implement/update actions must include a justification tied to the pattern.
  + context: Pattern-driven edits need explicit rationale to be auditable.
  + IF:
    Implement/update notes omit why the edit follows the pattern.
  + HOWEVER:
    Short notes are preferred to reduce overhead.
  + THEN:
    Require implement/update notes to state why the edit follows the pattern.
  + BECAUSE:
    Justified notes prevent unreasoned edits and make warnings meaningful.
  + NEXT-STEPS:
    - evidence: pattern-action implement/update notes include a rationale clause.
    - evidence-shape: {:action :string, :note :string, :pattern/id :string}
